# Forward every API call to the Render backend. CF Pages will proxy
# the request server-side, so the browser sees a normal same-origin
# response. This MUST come before the SPA catch-all so that POST/PUT/
# DELETE traffic doesn't get rewritten to /index.html.
/api/*    https://trynex-api.onrender.com/api/:splat    200

# Serve the live, DB-backed sitemap (every product, hamper, blog post,
# category) from the API. Bots requesting trynexshop.com/sitemap.xml
# get the always-fresh version. Note: a 200 rewrite does NOT fall back
# to the static /sitemap.xml in /public if the API is down — it returns
# the upstream error. The static files in /public exist for local dev
# and as a manually swappable safety net (change the rule to a 404
# fallback rewrite if the API outage is ever long-running).
/sitemap.xml    https://trynex-api.onrender.com/sitemap.xml    200
/robots.txt     https://trynex-api.onrender.com/robots.txt     200

# SPA fallback — every non-API path is served by index.html so client
# routing works on hard refresh.
/*        /index.html                                   200
